1
00:00:47,589 --> 00:00:49,590
GIRL:
Come, spirit.

2
00:00:51,801 --> 00:00:55,220
Help us sing the story of our land.

3
00:00:58,975 --> 00:01:01,602
You are our mother.

4
00:01:05,315 --> 00:01:07,983
We, your field of corn.

5
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:13,865
We rise...

6
00:01:14,658 --> 00:01:17,160
...from out of the soul of you.

7
00:04:04,748 --> 00:04:06,499
POCAHONTAS:
Dear Mother:

8
00:04:10,587 --> 00:04:13,589
You fill the land with your beauty.

9
00:04:20,597 --> 00:04:24,225
You reach to the end of the world.

10
00:04:28,563 --> 00:04:30,815
How shall I seek you?

11
00:04:35,821 --> 00:04:37,863
Show me your face.

12
00:04:41,828 --> 00:04:44,788
You, the great river...

13
00:04:45,873 --> 00:04:47,916
...that never runs dry.

14
00:06:16,423 --> 00:06:18,257
[WHISTLE BLOWING SOFTLY]

15
00:06:24,057 --> 00:06:26,058
[SPEAKING INAUDIBLY]

16
00:08:16,004 --> 00:08:17,838
[DRUM BEATING]

17
00:08:35,857 --> 00:08:37,733
Let him go.

18
00:08:37,901 --> 00:08:40,277
WINGFIELD:
You said to hang him, sir.

19
00:08:41,780 --> 00:08:43,489
Now remember, Smith.

20
00:08:43,657 --> 00:08:46,283
You've come to these shores in chains.

21
00:08:46,451 --> 00:08:48,410
You're under a cloud...

22
00:08:48,578 --> 00:08:53,332
...which will darken considerably if I hear
any more of your mutinous remarks.

23
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:55,585
Is that understood?

24
00:09:49,850 --> 00:09:53,477
Captain Newport, sir. I found oysters.

25
00:09:53,645 --> 00:09:56,606
They're as thick as my hands.
They're the size of stones, sir.

26
00:09:56,773 --> 00:09:59,442
And there's fish everywhere,
flapping against your legs.

27
00:09:59,610 --> 00:10:02,987
- We're gonna live like kings.
NEWPORT: All these months at sea.

28
00:10:03,155 --> 00:10:05,698
I'm weary of looking further.

29
00:10:05,866 --> 00:10:07,825
This place will serve.

30
00:10:07,993 --> 00:10:12,038
We have deep water to the shore,
we can see up and down the river.

31
00:10:12,205 --> 00:10:15,124
Our enemies will have
no advantage of surprise.

32
00:10:15,292 --> 00:10:18,461
Uh, bring the anchors
and, uh, midsails to shore...

33
00:10:18,629 --> 00:10:22,548
...in case some homesick persons
decide to slip away with them.

34
00:10:22,716 --> 00:10:24,342
[MEN CHUCKLE]

35
00:10:24,509 --> 00:10:27,386
We must be careful
not to offend the naturals.

36
00:10:27,596 --> 00:10:30,514
If our crops fail, we shall be obliged
to trade with them.

37
00:10:31,558 --> 00:10:35,353
Once we're established here,
we may go up the river...

38
00:10:36,313 --> 00:10:39,733
...and seek a route to the other sea.

39
00:10:47,116 --> 00:10:49,117
{AXES CHOPPING IN DISTANCE]

40
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:17,521
[SNIFFING]

41
00:11:31,870 --> 00:11:33,538
[HOLLERS]

42
00:11:42,464 --> 00:11:44,006
[SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

43
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:55,643
[HOLLERING]

44
00:11:58,105 --> 00:12:00,523
[IN ALGONQUIN]

45
00:12:04,695 --> 00:12:06,070
[POCAHONTAS GIGGLES]

46
00:12:11,910 --> 00:12:14,662
SMITH:
The savages often visit us kindly.

47
00:12:17,332 --> 00:12:20,335
Timid, like a herd of curious deer.

48
00:12:20,503 --> 00:12:21,837
[NATIVES SHOUTING]

49
00:12:22,005 --> 00:12:25,674
NEWPORT: Tonight we shall sleep
aboard our ships. Everyone in full armor.

50
00:12:25,842 --> 00:12:28,677
In the morning,
we will chop down every tree...

51
00:12:28,845 --> 00:12:32,347
...within half a mile of the moorage,
and use the straightest limbs...

52
00:12:32,515 --> 00:12:35,476
...to erect a line of watchtowers
and to build our fort.

53
00:12:35,643 --> 00:12:37,311
When we have done that...

54
00:12:37,479 --> 00:12:42,024
...we set our wheat and barley,
put up houses and lay in firewood.

55
00:12:42,192 --> 00:12:45,527
Slackers will be whipped
at the sight of their transgression.

56
00:12:45,695 --> 00:12:46,904
EMERY: Sir.
NEWPORT: Yes, Emery.

57
00:12:47,071 --> 00:12:49,531
EMERY:
When might we, uh, be going out to...

58
00:12:50,533 --> 00:12:52,534
...poke about, sir?

59
00:12:53,244 --> 00:12:55,871
NEWPORT:
We are not here to pillage and raid.

60
00:12:56,039 --> 00:13:00,375
We are here to establish a colony.

61
00:13:00,794 --> 00:13:02,795
SMITH:
How many lands behind me?

62
00:13:02,962 --> 00:13:04,880
NEWPORT:
Gold will do you no good.

63
00:13:05,048 --> 00:13:07,716
Not six months from now,
when the snow has begun to fly.

64
00:13:07,884 --> 00:13:09,802
SMITH:
How many seas?

65
00:13:14,809 --> 00:13:17,519
What blows and dangers?

66
00:13:23,818 --> 00:13:26,778
Fortune never my friend.

67
00:13:27,738 --> 00:13:29,739
[TOMOCOMO SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

68
00:14:02,606 --> 00:14:04,108
[SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

69
00:14:09,114 --> 00:14:10,114
[CROWS]

70
00:14:17,873 --> 00:14:19,582
[POCAHONTAS SCREAMS THEN LAUGHS]

71
00:14:26,590 --> 00:14:28,591
[POCAHONTAS GIGGLING]

72
00:15:27,735 --> 00:15:29,235
[MAN SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

73
00:15:45,462 --> 00:15:48,547
Five kegs is gone since we landed.
Somebody stole them.

74
00:15:48,715 --> 00:15:51,717
Rairs gotten to this, and worms here.

75
00:15:51,885 --> 00:15:52,885
NEWPORT:
Brand him.

76
00:15:53,053 --> 00:15:54,220
SELWAY:
And here.

77
00:15:55,055 --> 00:15:56,931
NEWPORT:
Cut off his ears.

78
00:15:59,601 --> 00:16:03,062
Captured these two, sir,
talking to the men.

79
00:16:03,230 --> 00:16:04,730
Spying.

80
00:16:11,738 --> 00:16:12,989
MAN:
Hey, you!

81
00:16:14,116 --> 00:16:16,117
[ALL MURMURING INDISTINCTLY]

82
00:16:17,786 --> 00:16:20,413
He stole me hatchet!

83
00:16:22,541 --> 00:16:23,833
[SHOUTS]

84
00:16:28,213 --> 00:16:31,007
NEWPORT:
We've lost the favor of the naturals.

85
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:34,844
Had we not sighted land
the day we did...

86
00:16:35,012 --> 00:16:37,139
...I would have turned back.

87
00:16:37,682 --> 00:16:40,392
We have eaten
the majority of our stores.

88
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:42,728
Our best men are sick with fever.

89
00:16:42,937 --> 00:16:44,813
The rest will soon breed mutiny.

90
00:16:44,981 --> 00:16:47,441
We might as well be shipwrecked.

91
00:16:48,776 --> 00:16:49,943
Now...

92
00:16:50,611 --> 00:16:55,282
...the naturals tell me
of a city up the river...

93
00:16:55,450 --> 00:16:59,202
...and of a mighty king who lives there.

94
00:16:59,370 --> 00:17:01,997
I propose we send
an envoy to this king...

95
00:17:02,165 --> 00:17:05,834
...to see whether he can be persuaded
to trade with us.

96
00:17:06,002 --> 00:17:10,964
Meanwhile, I shall, uh, return to England
for fresh supplies.

97
00:17:11,132 --> 00:17:12,924
I'll not be back until spring.

98
00:17:13,092 --> 00:17:16,470
Radcliffe here will be in command.

99
00:17:16,637 --> 00:17:21,266
As to who will approach
the savage king...

100
00:17:21,476 --> 00:17:24,853
...I needrt tell you
it will be a hazardous mission.

101
00:17:25,021 --> 00:17:27,689
ARGALL: Captain Smith
is the only professional soldier among us.

102
00:17:27,857 --> 00:17:31,986
Smith, sir? What are...?
What are his qualifications?

103
00:17:32,154 --> 00:17:33,237
ARGALL:
Those you lack.

104
00:17:33,405 --> 00:17:36,824
WINGFIELD: I should very dearly
like to know one thing.

105
00:17:36,992 --> 00:17:40,161
What is to prevent this friend
of the hangman...

106
00:17:40,329 --> 00:17:43,998
...from making league with the naturals
and turning upon us?

107
00:17:44,166 --> 00:17:47,418
Only under the extremity of torture,
I should like to assume.

108
00:17:47,586 --> 00:17:51,255
Or indeed instructing them in
the conduct of war and English strategies...

109
00:17:51,423 --> 00:17:53,966
...if I may make so bold.

110
00:17:54,676 --> 00:17:58,346
His right to the title of captaincy
is dubious at best.

111
00:17:58,514 --> 00:18:00,431
The lowborn son of a farmer...

112
00:18:00,599 --> 00:18:04,310
...cannot be expected to behave
with a gentlemars sense of propriety.

113
00:18:04,478 --> 00:18:06,312
Perhaps you'd like to go, Wingfield.

114
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:08,189
[ALL CHUCKLE]

115
00:18:08,357 --> 00:18:11,692
Smith, you have an opportunity
to repair your reputation.

116
00:18:12,361 --> 00:18:14,654
I expect you to welcome it.

117
00:18:43,726 --> 00:18:47,938
SMITH:
Who are you, whom I so faintly hear?

118
00:18:50,942 --> 00:18:53,360
Who urge me ever on?

119
00:18:54,070 --> 00:18:56,738
NEWPORT:
You have the makings of a leader, Smith.

120
00:18:57,574 --> 00:18:59,575
Can one rely on you?

121
00:19:16,051 --> 00:19:19,470
SMITH:
What voice is this that speaks within me?

122
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:25,518
Guides me towards the best?

123
00:19:42,411 --> 00:19:43,953
Where?

124
00:20:06,978 --> 00:20:09,688
Always the star was guiding me.

125
00:20:11,691 --> 00:20:13,275
Leading.

126
00:20:15,612 --> 00:20:17,571
Drawing me on.

127
00:20:21,493 --> 00:20:23,827
To the fabled land.

128
00:20:31,503 --> 00:20:33,879
There life shall begin.

129
00:20:46,977 --> 00:20:49,687
[HOLLERING]

130
00:20:51,231 --> 00:20:52,564
[HOLLERING IN DISTANCE]

131
00:21:05,913 --> 00:21:08,331
[HOLLERING]

132
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:37,694
A world equal to our hopes.

133
00:21:41,907 --> 00:21:45,536
A land where one might wash
one's soul pure.

134
00:21:48,623 --> 00:21:51,625
Rise to one's true stature.

135
00:22:01,094 --> 00:22:03,637
We shall make a new start.

136
00:22:05,932 --> 00:22:07,850
A fresh beginning.

137
00:22:13,774 --> 00:22:17,109
Here the blessings of the earth
are bestowed upon all.

138
00:22:19,905 --> 00:22:22,239
None need grow poor.

139
00:22:26,745 --> 00:22:29,747
Here there is good ground for all...

140
00:22:29,915 --> 00:22:32,625
...and no cost but one's labor.

141
00:22:35,379 --> 00:22:37,964
We shall build a true commonwealth.

142
00:22:38,132 --> 00:22:41,426
Hard work and self-reliance our virtues.

143
00:22:46,307 --> 00:22:48,934
We shall have no landlords
to rack us with high rents...

144
00:22:49,102 --> 00:22:51,520
...or extort the fruit of our labor.

145
00:22:57,485 --> 00:23:01,822
No man shall stand above any other.
We'll all live under the same law.

146
00:23:13,626 --> 00:23:17,003
Captain, we haven't the draft
to go any further.

147
00:23:18,381 --> 00:23:20,048
Put in.

148
00:23:44,074 --> 00:23:47,076
SMITH: None shall eat up carelessly
what his friends got won'thily...

149
00:23:47,244 --> 00:23:50,455
...or steal away that which virtue
has stored up.

150
00:23:54,001 --> 00:23:57,253
Men shall not make each other
their spoil.

151
00:23:57,754 --> 00:23:59,755
[HOLLERING IN DISTANCE]

152
00:24:00,924 --> 00:24:04,010
Let's go back, sir. Gather a larger party.

153
00:24:06,763 --> 00:24:08,514
We're lost.

154
00:24:11,059 --> 00:24:14,061
MAN: There the naturals go!
- Let him go!

155
00:25:22,633 --> 00:25:25,218
SELWAY:
Tide's run out, captain.

156
00:25:26,136 --> 00:25:28,721
Bottom's dragging on the mud, sir.

157
00:25:34,603 --> 00:25:36,271
SMITH:
Keep your matchlock lit.

158
00:25:36,438 --> 00:25:38,898
Fire a shot if you see anything.

159
00:25:47,116 --> 00:25:49,117
[BIRDS CALLING]

160
00:25:51,120 --> 00:25:53,121
[CRICKETS CLICKING]

161
00:26:57,730 --> 00:26:59,731
[DUCKS QUACKING IN DISTANCE]

162
00:27:09,909 --> 00:27:11,284
[SNAP]

163
00:27:20,586 --> 00:27:22,045
[GRUNTING]

164
00:27:26,676 --> 00:27:28,677
[NATIVES HOLLERING]

165
00:27:47,364 --> 00:27:49,365
[MAN SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

166
00:27:53,954 --> 00:27:55,955
SMITH:
The sun.

167
00:27:56,707 --> 00:27:58,833
And the moon as well.

168
00:28:01,253 --> 00:28:03,212
It shows you how the sun
chases the night...

169
00:28:03,380 --> 00:28:04,630
...continually around the world.

170
00:28:04,798 --> 00:28:06,757
[NATIVES CHATTERING IN ALGONQUIN]

171
00:28:35,872 --> 00:28:37,789
[NATIVES HOLLERING AND CHEERING]

172
00:29:21,876 --> 00:29:23,877
[NATIVES CHANTING]

173
00:29:31,136 --> 00:29:33,137
[MAN SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

174
00:29:51,990 --> 00:29:53,991
[SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

175
00:30:03,710 --> 00:30:07,588
The sky? No.

176
00:30:07,798 --> 00:30:11,717
From England, a land to the east.

177
00:30:25,400 --> 00:30:27,067
Leave?

178
00:30:28,403 --> 00:30:30,988
There won't be any leaving
till the spring.

179
00:30:31,155 --> 00:30:32,781
The boats won't be back till then.

180
00:30:38,454 --> 00:30:39,746
We have...

181
00:30:40,540 --> 00:30:42,916
...articles that might interest you.

182
00:30:46,337 --> 00:30:48,130
Gunpowder.

183
00:30:48,715 --> 00:30:50,340
[NATIVES GASP]

184
00:30:56,014 --> 00:30:58,015
[WHISPERING IN ALGONQUIN]

185
00:31:16,619 --> 00:31:18,411
[NATIVES HOLLERING]

186
00:31:31,467 --> 00:31:35,511
SMITH: At the moment I was to die,
she threw herself upon me.

187
00:31:44,521 --> 00:31:46,189
[IN ALGONQUIN]

188
00:31:57,868 --> 00:31:59,995
PARAHUNT:

189
00:32:10,924 --> 00:32:12,925
[WOMAN SOBBING]

190
00:32:15,053 --> 00:32:17,054
POWHATAN:

191
00:32:48,795 --> 00:32:50,796
[NATIVES CHEERING]

192
00:34:26,478 --> 00:34:28,479
[NATIVES CHANTING IN DISTANCE]

193
00:35:32,796 --> 00:35:34,797
[CHILDREN GIGGLING]

194
00:35:36,091 --> 00:35:37,675
[SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

195
00:35:39,928 --> 00:35:43,389
SMITH: Sky.
- Sky.

196
00:35:44,641 --> 00:35:46,184
[SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

197
00:35:52,274 --> 00:35:55,276
- Sun.
- Sun.

198
00:35:56,069 --> 00:35:57,987
[SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

199
00:36:04,244 --> 00:36:05,286
Water.

200
00:36:09,124 --> 00:36:15,254
Wind. Wind.

201
00:36:32,941 --> 00:36:34,733
[SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

202
00:36:44,702 --> 00:36:49,039
Eyes.

203
00:36:52,210 --> 00:36:53,669
[SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

204
00:37:00,176 --> 00:37:04,721
Lips.

205
00:37:15,234 --> 00:37:16,526
[SMITH CLEARS THROAT]

206
00:37:17,152 --> 00:37:18,695
Ear.

207
00:37:39,174 --> 00:37:42,802
SMITH: All the children of the king
were beautiful, but she...

208
00:37:42,970 --> 00:37:45,388
...the youngest, was so exceedingly so...

209
00:37:45,556 --> 00:37:48,599
...that the sun himself,
though he saw her often...

210
00:37:48,767 --> 00:37:52,520
...was surprised whenever she came out
into his presence.

211
00:37:58,402 --> 00:38:03,032
Her father had a dozen wives,
a hundred children...

212
00:38:03,199 --> 00:38:05,409
...but she was his favorite.

213
00:38:11,750 --> 00:38:14,585
She exceeded the rest
not only in feature and proportion...

214
00:38:14,753 --> 00:38:17,296
...but in wit and spirit too.

215
00:38:23,053 --> 00:38:25,387
All loved her.

216
00:38:31,603 --> 00:38:33,062
Moon.

217
00:38:40,612 --> 00:38:42,613
[HOLLERING AND LAUGHING]

218
00:39:28,160 --> 00:39:29,661
[SHOUTS]

219
00:40:17,878 --> 00:40:22,882
SMITH:
They are gentle, loving, faithful...

220
00:40:23,049 --> 00:40:26,093
...lacking in all guile and trickery.

221
00:40:28,889 --> 00:40:33,602
The words denoting
lying, deceit, greed...

222
00:40:33,769 --> 00:40:36,688
...envy, slander and forgiveness
have never been heard.

223
00:40:40,610 --> 00:40:45,405
They have no jealousy,
no sense of possession.

224
00:40:52,914 --> 00:40:57,542
Real, what I thought a dream.

225
00:42:12,703 --> 00:42:15,789
POWHATAN [IN ALGONQUIN]:

226
00:42:27,844 --> 00:42:30,178
POWHATAN:

227
00:42:52,535 --> 00:42:54,620
SMITH:
I am not guarded.

228
00:43:16,810 --> 00:43:18,394
They trust me as a brother.

229
00:43:18,562 --> 00:43:20,063
Heat.

230
00:43:20,230 --> 00:43:22,231
POCAHONTAS: Heat. Heat.
SMITH: Heat.

231
00:43:22,399 --> 00:43:27,236
I, who was a pirate
who lived to steal what I could.

232
00:43:30,199 --> 00:43:32,367
I am a free man now.

233
00:43:37,581 --> 00:43:39,332
All that they have is given me.

234
00:43:41,669 --> 00:43:46,839
I don't know.

235
00:43:47,007 --> 00:43:49,008
[SHOUTING]

236
00:43:56,266 --> 00:43:58,519
[MAN SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

237
00:44:06,444 --> 00:44:08,445
[CHILD COUGHING]

238
00:44:14,411 --> 00:44:16,412
[NATIVES MURMURING IN ALGONQUIN]

239
00:44:33,555 --> 00:44:35,597
SMITH:
Saved a child from drowning.

240
00:44:38,893 --> 00:44:41,061
Never had it struck me
so forcefully before...

241
00:44:41,229 --> 00:44:44,732
...that I have the power to grant
life and health to others.

242
00:46:53,114 --> 00:46:54,865
Lawless.

243
00:47:05,626 --> 00:47:07,794
I was a dead man.

244
00:47:10,464 --> 00:47:12,299
Now I live.

245
00:47:23,312 --> 00:47:25,187
You, my light.

246
00:47:29,026 --> 00:47:30,943
My America.

247
00:47:38,911 --> 00:47:40,244
Love.

248
00:47:44,666 --> 00:47:47,418
Shall we deny it when it visits us?

249
00:47:52,549 --> 00:47:55,384
Shall we not take what we are given?

250
00:48:14,697 --> 00:48:17,324
There is only this.

251
00:48:19,327 --> 00:48:22,120
All else is unreal.

252
00:48:35,385 --> 00:48:37,052
POCAHONTAS:
Mother...

253
00:48:39,722 --> 00:48:42,015
...where do you live?

254
00:48:45,353 --> 00:48:47,854
In the sky?

255
00:48:49,691 --> 00:48:52,025
The clouds?

256
00:48:53,736 --> 00:48:56,029
The sea?

257
00:49:08,460 --> 00:49:10,878
Give me a sign.

258
00:49:19,513 --> 00:49:26,102
We rise.

259
00:49:27,312 --> 00:49:28,938
[SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

260
00:49:40,617 --> 00:49:43,578
POCAHONTAS:
Afraid of myself.

261
00:49:48,292 --> 00:49:51,294
A god, he seems to me.

262
00:50:01,931 --> 00:50:06,393
What else is life but being near you?

263
00:50:11,983 --> 00:50:13,817
Do they suspect?

264
00:50:18,156 --> 00:50:20,991
Oh, to be given to you...

265
00:50:23,119 --> 00:50:25,496
...you to me.

266
00:50:25,663 --> 00:50:27,664
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

267
00:50:33,671 --> 00:50:35,255
I will be faithful to you.

268
00:50:38,259 --> 00:50:39,927
True.

269
00:50:56,612 --> 00:50:59,197
Two no more.

270
00:51:00,449 --> 00:51:06,538
One.

271
00:51:09,125 --> 00:51:14,879
I am.

272
00:51:19,844 --> 00:51:21,261
[MAN SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

273
00:51:40,407 --> 00:51:42,825
SMITH:
The king announced that I was free.

274
00:51:42,993 --> 00:51:45,244
He was sending me back.

275
00:51:45,745 --> 00:51:48,038
And on the understanding
that when spring came...

276
00:51:48,248 --> 00:51:50,749
...we were to go back
to where we came from.

277
00:51:53,420 --> 00:51:56,505
His chiefs had advised him to kill me.

278
00:51:57,257 --> 00:52:01,552
I had gained a knowledge of their arms,
their strong places.

279
00:52:02,762 --> 00:52:05,764
But his daughter assured him
I was a good man.

280
00:52:21,364 --> 00:52:24,283
I should tell people
that though the naturals lived in peace...

281
00:52:24,451 --> 00:52:28,412
...they yet were strong and would not
suffer their land to be taken away.

282
00:52:29,956 --> 00:52:32,792
There was no sea
beyond the mountains.

283
00:52:33,502 --> 00:52:37,422
Only a land stretching away forever
in great meadows.

284
00:52:37,798 --> 00:52:40,133
A land which had no end.

285
00:53:37,651 --> 00:53:39,652
Captain Smith.

286
00:53:41,822 --> 00:53:43,823
You're back.

287
00:53:46,243 --> 00:53:48,911
The savages will have
to stop here, captain.

288
00:53:50,956 --> 00:53:52,373
[SMITH SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

289
00:54:25,742 --> 00:54:28,076
- Where have you been?
- It's like seeing a ghost.

290
00:54:28,244 --> 00:54:30,620
BOY 3: You look like you've come back
from the dead.

291
00:54:30,788 --> 00:54:32,497
- Where's Captain Radcliffe?
BOY 2: No word.

292
00:54:32,665 --> 00:54:35,584
BOY 1: Shut your mouth!
BOY 2: People say he went over to England.

293
00:54:35,752 --> 00:54:37,419
BOY 3: Did you bring food?
BOY 1: Starving.

294
00:54:37,587 --> 00:54:40,339
SMITH: I brought food.
BOY 1: Someone got killed. Just fell over.

295
00:54:40,506 --> 00:54:42,466
BOY 2:
Four months of stealing and stealing.

296
00:54:42,633 --> 00:54:44,551
BOY 3: Look at him. Bastard.
BOY 2: Get up.

297
00:54:44,719 --> 00:54:46,720
[BOYS CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

298
00:54:47,597 --> 00:54:49,806
Gambling. They bowl
while the houses fall down.

299
00:54:49,974 --> 00:54:52,768
- Look at the church.
BOY 2: Sickness coming in from the marsh.

300
00:54:52,935 --> 00:54:54,728
SMITH: Who's taking care of you?
BOYS: No one.

301
00:54:54,896 --> 00:54:57,105
It's all just dying and sickness
and all that.

302
00:54:57,273 --> 00:54:59,191
- I saw a body in the mud.
- You're a liar.

303
00:54:59,359 --> 00:55:01,276
- I saw a leg in the bed.
- You are a liar.

304
00:55:01,444 --> 00:55:04,529
- Four people died last night.
- Why was the leg in the bed?

305
00:55:04,697 --> 00:55:07,658
Thieves! Jackals! Lash their feet!

306
00:55:11,038 --> 00:55:15,124
You're looking rather well, Smith.
Been enjoying yourself, have you?

307
00:55:15,292 --> 00:55:19,754
Been enjoying yourself mightily,
I expect.

308
00:55:20,339 --> 00:55:22,256
You were sent to relieve our situation...

309
00:55:22,424 --> 00:55:24,967
...not to pleasure yourself.
We here have suffered.

310
00:55:25,135 --> 00:55:27,678
SMITH: I'll ignore the stories
which bring officials disrepute.

311
00:55:27,846 --> 00:55:30,640
No speeches, Smith.
Things are different now.

312
00:55:32,309 --> 00:55:34,394
We can't allow cheek.

313
00:55:34,561 --> 00:55:37,397
Allow cheek, and we shall have chaos.
I wear the medal now.

314
00:55:37,564 --> 00:55:40,483
I am president and you have been
stripped of your captaincy.

315
00:55:40,651 --> 00:55:42,485
SMITH:
Are you qualified to pass judgment on me?

316
00:55:42,653 --> 00:55:45,363
That needrt concern us at the moment.

317
00:55:45,656 --> 00:55:48,825
Pity you were not here at the time
of your trial to defend yourself.

318
00:55:48,992 --> 00:55:53,162
I presume you were too afraid,
too guilty to return.

319
00:55:54,039 --> 00:55:56,375
SMITH: My trial?
- Yes.

320
00:55:56,543 --> 00:55:58,919
You were indicted
upon a chapter in Leviticus...

321
00:55:59,087 --> 00:56:02,005
...and tried during the period
of your desertion.

322
00:56:02,173 --> 00:56:03,799
Our law is speedy here.

323
00:56:03,967 --> 00:56:06,343
ARGALL: Been keeping all the good food
for himself, Smith.

324
00:56:06,511 --> 00:56:08,011
Giving us rotten corn.

325
00:56:08,179 --> 00:56:10,055
You, sir, have no other eyes and ears...

326
00:56:10,223 --> 00:56:12,391
...than those which grow
on Smith's head here.

327
00:56:12,559 --> 00:56:14,810
LEWES:
He does nothing but tend his own pot.

328
00:56:14,978 --> 00:56:17,896
I have shared all.
I have kept nothing for myself.

329
00:56:18,064 --> 00:56:20,524
- Nothing!
- His name is not even Wingfield.

330
00:56:20,692 --> 00:56:23,944
It's Woodson. Woodson is the name.

331
00:56:24,487 --> 00:56:26,655
Left England under a cloud of disgrace.

332
00:56:26,823 --> 00:56:29,491
Seize them. Seize them!

333
00:56:30,660 --> 00:56:35,873
Any man impeding the punishment of
these rogues will be dealt with harshly.

334
00:56:39,252 --> 00:56:40,878
Here.

335
00:56:42,881 --> 00:56:46,049
There's no sense in waiting for a trial.
This is mutiny.

336
00:56:46,217 --> 00:56:48,511
I dispatch you herewith
in the name of the king.

337
00:56:49,138 --> 00:56:50,555
[MEN GASP]

338
00:56:55,895 --> 00:56:58,605
LEWES:
Dead as an herring. Serves him right.

339
00:56:58,772 --> 00:57:01,149
MAN 1:
I can ratify what Mr. Argall said.

340
00:57:01,317 --> 00:57:04,652
I should be ashamed to let my servant
keep company with such fellows.

341
00:57:04,820 --> 00:57:06,488
You were a servant.

342
00:57:06,655 --> 00:57:08,990
I ate a single chicken,
and that when I were ill.

343
00:57:09,158 --> 00:57:11,618
Small has eaten six,
which he could not be troubled...

344
00:57:11,785 --> 00:57:13,620
MAN 2:
I say it's Captain Smith should lead us.

345
00:57:13,787 --> 00:57:15,830
ALL:
Aye.

346
00:57:55,163 --> 00:57:57,164
SMITH:
Tell her.

347
00:57:59,209 --> 00:58:01,710
Tell her what?

348
00:58:04,714 --> 00:58:06,507
I love you.

349
00:58:08,593 --> 00:58:11,011
But I cannot love you.

350
00:58:33,202 --> 00:58:35,078
It was a dream.

351
00:58:37,623 --> 00:58:39,833
Now I am awake.

352
00:58:41,669 --> 00:58:43,628
MAN:
What do you want with him?

353
00:58:46,632 --> 00:58:49,718
- What should we do with him?
SMITH: Nothing.

354
00:58:51,178 --> 00:58:52,887
He's mad.

355
00:58:54,015 --> 00:58:55,599
Harmless.

356
00:59:22,711 --> 00:59:24,378
It's yours.

357
00:59:24,921 --> 00:59:26,547
You know...

358
01:00:20,561 --> 01:00:22,312
[MEN CHUCKLING]

359
01:00:38,413 --> 01:00:41,373
GENERAL:
Withdraw! March!

360
01:00:41,541 --> 01:00:43,375
- March!
MEN: St. George! St. George!

361
01:00:43,543 --> 01:00:45,669
GENERAL: March!
MEN: St. George! St. George!

362
01:00:45,837 --> 01:00:47,838
[MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

363
01:00:58,641 --> 01:01:01,101
SMITH:
I let her love me.

364
01:01:08,318 --> 01:01:10,695
I made her love me.

365
01:01:12,823 --> 01:01:14,615
And what was your disagreement about?

366
01:01:14,783 --> 01:01:18,494
He said today is the 15th of October.
I said the 17th.

367
01:01:18,662 --> 01:01:20,413
SMITH:
I must.

368
01:01:21,165 --> 01:01:25,209
You were fighting
about the day of the year?

369
01:01:25,377 --> 01:01:26,753
Damnation is like this.

370
01:01:26,920 --> 01:01:30,173
Didrt I tell you to dig a new well
farther from the shore?

371
01:01:30,799 --> 01:01:32,759
Why hasn't this been done?

372
01:01:34,303 --> 01:01:37,847
Every man must stop what he's doing
right now and start digging the well!

373
01:01:38,015 --> 01:01:40,475
Those of you that can't carry
the dirt in buckets...

374
01:01:40,642 --> 01:01:42,477
...shall carry it with your own hands.

375
01:01:42,644 --> 01:01:45,730
He that will not work shall not eat.

376
01:01:45,898 --> 01:01:48,649
The labors of honest
and industrious men...

377
01:01:48,817 --> 01:01:52,278
...shall not be consumed
to maintain the idleness of a few.

378
01:01:52,446 --> 01:01:56,116
The country is to them a misery,
a death...

379
01:01:56,284 --> 01:01:58,202
...a hell.

380
01:01:59,412 --> 01:02:01,371
MAN:
Mind yourself, mate.

381
01:02:13,802 --> 01:02:16,720
SMITH:
While they starve, they dig for gold.

382
01:02:20,266 --> 01:02:25,354
There is no talk, no hope,
no work but this.

383
01:02:31,402 --> 01:02:34,738
If there's so much gold,
why don't the naturals have any?

384
01:02:34,906 --> 01:02:37,407
You're chasing a dream.

385
01:02:37,575 --> 01:02:41,787
You see what men they've sent us.
A headless multitude.

386
01:02:42,038 --> 01:02:43,831
They will not sow corn
for their own bellies.

387
01:02:43,998 --> 01:02:48,336
They will rather eat their fish raw
than fetch some wood to dress it.

388
01:02:50,256 --> 01:02:51,756
Bad water.

389
01:02:52,758 --> 01:02:54,717
Sturgeon gone.

390
01:02:56,345 --> 01:02:57,720
Mutterings.

391
01:02:57,888 --> 01:03:00,223
They shall plant vineyards
and drink the wine.

392
01:03:00,391 --> 01:03:05,228
I will raise up the tent of David...
Love good and hate evil.

393
01:03:05,396 --> 01:03:08,189
...and close up the breaches of his tent.

394
01:03:08,357 --> 01:03:12,569
Take away from me the noise
of your music and your songs...

395
01:03:12,778 --> 01:03:16,155
...so I will not hear the melody.
The Lord has given the command...

396
01:03:16,323 --> 01:03:19,325
...and he will smash
the large house into pieces...

397
01:03:19,493 --> 01:03:21,452
...and the small house into bits!

398
01:03:21,620 --> 01:03:23,454
Somebody should shoot Small there.

399
01:03:23,622 --> 01:03:27,166
He hasn't got a ghost of a chance,
and he'll contaminate us all.

400
01:03:27,334 --> 01:03:32,171
He used Wortham's spoon,
now Wortham's gone, my friend.

401
01:03:32,339 --> 01:03:34,132
Have we gotta wait until all is dead?

402
01:03:54,487 --> 01:03:57,990
Sir, Ackley's dead.

403
01:03:58,158 --> 01:04:00,659
Somebody ate his hands.

404
01:04:02,454 --> 01:04:05,623
Went out in the height of style, anyhow.

405
01:04:05,832 --> 01:04:11,003
Such tranquility,
you'd think he could speak.

406
01:04:11,171 --> 01:04:15,132
I shall miss him. I think we all shall.

407
01:04:19,095 --> 01:04:20,930
We're 38 now.

408
01:04:39,367 --> 01:04:42,077
SMITH:
To go back up that river.

409
01:04:45,247 --> 01:04:47,707
To love her in the wild.

410
01:04:56,801 --> 01:04:58,760
What holds you here?

411
01:05:04,684 --> 01:05:07,602
What are your intentions towards her?

412
01:05:11,607 --> 01:05:13,984
Towards them?

413
01:05:14,151 --> 01:05:16,152
[SHIVERING]

414
01:05:20,742 --> 01:05:23,577
BOY 1: There's nothing in the river.
The river's empty.

415
01:05:26,498 --> 01:05:29,250
We wanna go back to England.
Please, can we?

416
01:05:30,585 --> 01:05:33,254
- Where's Captain Newport?
- There's nothing to eat.

417
01:05:33,422 --> 01:05:35,131
SMITH:
Captain Newport will be back shortly.

418
01:05:35,298 --> 01:05:36,340
BOY 1:
Will he have food?

419
01:05:36,508 --> 01:05:39,510
SMITH: He'd better.
- When will we go back to England?

420
01:05:39,678 --> 01:05:41,387
They're eating all the dead.

421
01:05:41,555 --> 01:05:43,389
BOY 2:
Do you believe in ghosts, captain?

422
01:05:43,557 --> 01:05:46,726
People don't care
about the Indians no more.

423
01:06:45,661 --> 01:06:47,662
[NATIVES CHATTERING IN ALGONQUIN]

424
01:07:15,692 --> 01:07:18,194
Don't put yourself in danger.

425
01:07:19,154 --> 01:07:21,656
You don't have to do anything else...

426
01:07:21,824 --> 01:07:23,699
...for us.

427
01:07:24,618 --> 01:07:27,036
Why have you not come to me?

428
01:07:40,843 --> 01:07:42,468
SMITH:
I know, my love.

429
01:07:47,641 --> 01:07:49,142
Don't trust me.

430
01:07:55,024 --> 01:07:57,651
You don't know who I am.

431
01:08:22,677 --> 01:08:24,845
Remember.

432
01:08:59,465 --> 01:09:02,133
MAN 1: Thank you.
MAN 2: God be with you.

433
01:09:02,301 --> 01:09:05,720
MAN 3: God bless.
MAN 4: May almighty God bless you.

434
01:09:05,930 --> 01:09:08,348
MAN 2:
May God be with you.

435
01:09:08,515 --> 01:09:10,475
MAN 1:
Thank you, thank you, thank you.

436
01:09:10,643 --> 01:09:12,810
MAN 5:
Thank you, kindly.

437
01:09:25,741 --> 01:09:29,494
POCAHONTAS:
Who are you, whom I love?

438
01:09:41,341 --> 01:09:42,925
SMITH:
She.

439
01:09:45,512 --> 01:09:47,805
Brass twitched her hand.

440
01:09:51,685 --> 01:09:53,978
- Where are you going?
SMITH: Crabs in a bucket.

441
01:09:54,145 --> 01:09:55,771
Where you would not dare to follow.

442
01:09:55,939 --> 01:09:58,357
Scuttling over each other.

443
01:09:58,733 --> 01:10:02,695
- Don't you think you should take more men?
- They can come if they choose.

444
01:10:02,862 --> 01:10:05,739
I will see if we can trade
with another tribe.

445
01:10:06,199 --> 01:10:09,034
Sail. Sail on.

446
01:10:09,202 --> 01:10:11,370
Be careful, sir.

447
01:10:17,419 --> 01:10:20,087
SMITH:
What else is life but living there?

448
01:10:24,050 --> 01:10:25,884
Steal her love.

449
01:10:33,060 --> 01:10:35,312
She lay in peace...

450
01:10:35,479 --> 01:10:37,731
...gazed at the sky.

451
01:10:41,110 --> 01:10:42,736
Motionless.

452
01:10:46,407 --> 01:10:47,866
Afraid of what I most desire.

453
01:10:48,617 --> 01:10:50,702
Fool I was.

454
01:10:55,207 --> 01:10:57,959
Cannot walk two paths at once.
Leave her free.

455
01:10:58,127 --> 01:11:01,963
Ride two horses. Can't deceive the good.

456
01:11:10,222 --> 01:11:12,265
Cling to the good.

457
01:11:13,559 --> 01:11:15,602
As long as you do,
you have a claim in life.

458
01:11:22,027 --> 01:11:23,569
[MAN SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

459
01:11:23,737 --> 01:11:25,821
She, unbound.

460
01:11:49,096 --> 01:11:50,262
The source of all evil.

461
01:11:53,141 --> 01:11:55,351
It excuses vulgarity.

462
01:11:55,519 --> 01:11:58,562
Makes wrong right, base noble.

463
01:11:59,606 --> 01:12:01,607
[SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

464
01:13:03,630 --> 01:13:05,756
There's something I know
when I'm with you...

465
01:13:05,924 --> 01:13:08,176
...that I forget when I'm away.

466
01:13:10,012 --> 01:13:12,096
Tell me, my love...

467
01:13:13,015 --> 01:13:16,058
...did you wish for me
to come back and live with you again?

468
01:13:45,714 --> 01:13:47,548
POCAHONTAS:
True.

469
01:13:48,008 --> 01:13:50,134
Shut your eyes.

470
01:13:56,309 --> 01:13:58,936
Is this the man I loved?

471
01:13:59,771 --> 01:14:01,563
So long.

472
01:14:03,942 --> 01:14:05,901
A ghost.

473
01:14:10,865 --> 01:14:12,324
Come.

474
01:14:18,498 --> 01:14:20,749
Where are you, my love?

475
01:14:31,803 --> 01:14:34,263
Free.

476
01:14:44,357 --> 01:14:46,651
What do I fear?

477
01:14:56,161 --> 01:14:58,580
Can love lie?

478
01:15:06,046 --> 01:15:07,630
You.

479
01:15:17,141 --> 01:15:19,642
We can't go into the forest.

480
01:15:22,396 --> 01:15:24,564
Could I show you England?

481
01:15:28,193 --> 01:15:30,528
Oh, it's too far.

482
01:15:33,991 --> 01:15:36,535
If I can be with you...

483
01:15:40,790 --> 01:15:42,666
...that is all.

484
01:16:32,635 --> 01:16:34,594
SMITH:
That fort is not the world.

485
01:16:40,685 --> 01:16:43,436
The river leads back there.

486
01:16:45,147 --> 01:16:47,482
It leads onward too.

487
01:16:48,109 --> 01:16:50,068
Deeper.

488
01:16:52,029 --> 01:16:54,364
Into the wild.

489
01:16:57,493 --> 01:16:59,786
Start over.

490
01:17:03,958 --> 01:17:07,585
Exchange this false life for a true one.

491
01:17:10,214 --> 01:17:12,799
Give up the name of Smith.

492
01:17:41,747 --> 01:17:42,913
What are you doing here?

493
01:17:44,166 --> 01:17:47,835
Beg your pardon, sir.
You were gone longer than we expected.

494
01:17:48,295 --> 01:17:50,755
Appears I've wandered off myself a bit.

495
01:17:51,631 --> 01:17:53,674
Things go badly?

496
01:17:59,514 --> 01:18:01,348
SMITH:
No ties.

497
01:18:05,103 --> 01:18:07,396
Space enough at last.

498
01:18:07,689 --> 01:18:09,482
Break free.

499
01:18:10,610 --> 01:18:13,320
Can I lead them off some other way?

500
01:18:23,706 --> 01:18:26,541
What about the soil, captain?
Is it as good as we thought?

501
01:18:28,044 --> 01:18:29,711
- Not really.
- Always alone.

502
01:18:29,879 --> 01:18:32,964
In fact, I've rarely seen such a pest hole.

503
01:18:33,132 --> 01:18:35,175
Look about you, everything's swamp.

504
01:18:35,343 --> 01:18:38,011
Water standing in lakes and pools
so the ground gives way.

505
01:18:38,179 --> 01:18:39,471
Let the dead bury the dead.

506
01:18:39,639 --> 01:18:42,224
I suspect there's more puddles
than dry land.

507
01:18:42,391 --> 01:18:45,143
Each producing more mosquitoes
in their slime...

508
01:18:45,311 --> 01:18:48,021
...and each mosquito
is hungry as a priest.

509
01:18:48,564 --> 01:18:50,899
None but a savage
could inabit the place.

510
01:18:52,318 --> 01:18:53,985
But west of here...

511
01:18:54,153 --> 01:18:57,197
...towards the mountains, or south,
that is something else.

512
01:18:57,824 --> 01:18:59,282
- We could sail on.
POCAHONTAS: Come...

513
01:18:59,450 --> 01:19:01,911
SMITH: Seek a passage to the east.
POCAHONTAS: My love.

514
01:19:03,872 --> 01:19:05,540
It flows.

515
01:19:08,252 --> 01:19:10,878
Where? Life.

516
01:19:14,299 --> 01:19:15,341
Are you true?

517
01:19:15,509 --> 01:19:20,555
We, in your soul. Life.

518
01:19:20,722 --> 01:19:22,139
[GIGGLING]

519
01:19:23,183 --> 01:19:25,393
Am I to see them?

520
01:19:26,103 --> 01:19:28,020
My mouth is dry.

521
01:19:31,483 --> 01:19:33,943
My body trembles.

522
01:19:37,781 --> 01:19:40,283
My skin burns.

523
01:19:42,786 --> 01:19:44,620
I have two minds.

524
01:19:47,916 --> 01:19:50,126
Should I tell Father?

525
01:19:51,587 --> 01:19:54,131
There is nothing but this.

526
01:19:57,635 --> 01:19:59,595
What was I?

527
01:20:04,809 --> 01:20:05,976
What am I now?

528
01:20:08,730 --> 01:20:10,731
Oh, Mother.

529
01:20:11,983 --> 01:20:13,817
What have I done?

530
01:20:14,319 --> 01:20:17,195
Love is unbound by limits.

531
01:20:22,243 --> 01:20:24,953
This love is like pain.

532
01:20:27,040 --> 01:20:28,707
I am...

533
01:20:29,375 --> 01:20:31,460
...I shall be...

534
01:20:32,462 --> 01:20:34,254
...yours.

535
01:21:00,324 --> 01:21:02,700
POWHATAN [IN ALGONQUIN]:

536
01:21:16,006 --> 01:21:17,382
[POWHATAN SHOUTS]

537
01:21:23,931 --> 01:21:25,932
[NATIVES HOLLERING]

538
01:21:55,839 --> 01:21:57,840
Come away.

539
01:22:01,803 --> 01:22:03,804
You must tell me why.

540
01:22:06,933 --> 01:22:11,937
- They can't hear. I've sent them away.
- He sees you mean to stay.

541
01:22:22,115 --> 01:22:24,116
They're coming.

542
01:22:28,789 --> 01:22:31,207
Make peace with him.

543
01:22:31,417 --> 01:22:33,835
He won't accept peace.

544
01:22:34,003 --> 01:22:35,795
Why would he?

545
01:22:43,971 --> 01:22:47,015
- Come away.
- And where would we live?

546
01:22:49,477 --> 01:22:51,311
In the woods?

547
01:22:52,563 --> 01:22:54,314
On a treetop?

548
01:22:54,482 --> 01:22:55,982
A hole in the ground?

549
01:23:16,670 --> 01:23:20,216
You have to come with me into the fort.

550
01:23:20,425 --> 01:23:23,719
Your people will know you came here.
They'll find out soon enough.

551
01:24:47,638 --> 01:24:49,639
[MEN WHISPERING IN ALGONQUIN]

552
01:24:51,809 --> 01:24:53,810
[GUNFIRE AND SHOUTING]

553
01:25:14,124 --> 01:25:15,833
GENERAL:
Go! On the double, gentlemen!

554
01:25:16,084 --> 01:25:17,418
MEN:
God save the king!

555
01:25:17,586 --> 01:25:24,300
GENERAL: Port your pikes!
MEN: God save the king!

556
01:25:24,468 --> 01:25:25,801
Charge!

557
01:25:25,969 --> 01:25:30,306
And on the Swiss step,
gentlemen, march!

558
01:25:30,474 --> 01:25:33,976
MEN: St. George,
St. George, St. George, St. George...

559
01:25:34,144 --> 01:25:36,479
- Prepare to stand!
MEN: St. George, St. George...

560
01:25:36,647 --> 01:25:37,980
- Stand!
MEN: St. George!

561
01:25:38,148 --> 01:25:40,149
GENERAL:
Musketeers, advance!

562
01:25:41,610 --> 01:25:43,611
Fire!

563
01:25:46,114 --> 01:25:48,115
[NATIVES HOLLERING AND SHOUTING]

564
01:25:55,083 --> 01:25:56,959
[GRUNTING AND SHOUTING]

565
01:26:02,382 --> 01:26:06,134
Hold the ground! Hold together, men!

566
01:27:40,899 --> 01:27:42,900
[SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

567
01:27:57,624 --> 01:27:59,625
[MEN SHOUTING]

568
01:28:00,168 --> 01:28:02,169
[GRUNTING]

569
01:28:05,131 --> 01:28:08,175
SELWAY: You're like a herd of deer!
- What are you waiting for?

570
01:28:08,343 --> 01:28:10,844
How can you own land?
This earth was made for such...

571
01:28:11,012 --> 01:28:13,722
...that shall improve it
and knows how to live!

572
01:28:13,890 --> 01:28:15,474
[SHOUTING IN ALGONQUIN]

573
01:28:15,642 --> 01:28:18,435
MAN: They have no sound, sir,
but I couldn't...

574
01:28:18,603 --> 01:28:20,104
Fire on him!

575
01:28:20,271 --> 01:28:23,315
What are you waiting for? Fire on him!

576
01:28:23,483 --> 01:28:25,192
You heathen bastards!

577
01:28:25,360 --> 01:28:27,987
MAN:
Please don't. Please. Please.

578
01:28:29,323 --> 01:28:31,032
Seeds of sulfur!

579
01:28:31,242 --> 01:28:35,161
Sons of fire!
Devils in the mouth of hell!

580
01:28:35,329 --> 01:28:37,414
MAN:
Please don't, please don't, please don't.

581
01:28:37,706 --> 01:28:39,082
[NATIVE GRUNTS]

582
01:28:43,170 --> 01:28:45,171
[NATIVES HOLLERING]

583
01:28:48,676 --> 01:28:51,344
Retreat! Fall back!

584
01:29:14,410 --> 01:29:16,077
SMITH:
Lord...

585
01:29:16,245 --> 01:29:18,456
...turn not away thy face.

586
01:29:21,710 --> 01:29:23,043
[GUNSHOT]

587
01:29:25,839 --> 01:29:28,883
You desire not the death of a sinner.

588
01:29:30,385 --> 01:29:32,470
I have gone away from you.

589
01:29:35,682 --> 01:29:38,225
I have not harkened to your voice.

590
01:29:38,393 --> 01:29:40,102
[GRUNTING AND SHOUTING]

591
01:29:40,854 --> 01:29:42,396
Let us not be brought to nothing.

592
01:29:42,564 --> 01:29:46,567
MAN 1: Gather reinforcements!
MAN 2: They're climbing up the wall!

593
01:30:02,250 --> 01:30:04,251
[GUNFIRE ECHOING]

594
01:30:20,394 --> 01:30:22,604
[IN ALGONQUIN]

595
01:31:49,610 --> 01:31:51,612
[ALL HOLLERING]

596
01:31:54,657 --> 01:32:16,720
[GUNSHOT]

597
01:32:34,072 --> 01:32:36,198
MAN:
The water is poison.

598
01:32:37,575 --> 01:32:40,243
They put a dead dog in the well.

599
01:32:41,913 --> 01:32:44,957
Can't go out to look for fish or game.

600
01:32:48,754 --> 01:32:50,922
How long can we last?

601
01:32:53,967 --> 01:32:56,260
Starvation does fearful things to a man.

602
01:32:56,428 --> 01:32:58,179
SMITH:
I hate your hearts.

603
01:32:58,347 --> 01:33:00,682
I'm not sure I should have
the use of this hand again.

604
01:33:00,849 --> 01:33:02,934
SMITH:
My value is the carcasses
of unburied men.

605
01:33:03,102 --> 01:33:05,603
Something you're not telling us.
I got a right to know.

606
01:33:05,771 --> 01:33:08,272
- What was they shouting?
SMITH: Tired of your contempt.

607
01:33:08,440 --> 01:33:10,233
SELWAY:
What did you do to them?

608
01:33:10,401 --> 01:33:12,151
SMITH:
You don't know where you are.

609
01:33:12,319 --> 01:33:14,696
Something you're not telling us.

610
01:33:15,698 --> 01:33:17,782
SMITH:
Like a wasp in a bottle.

611
01:33:19,284 --> 01:33:20,868
Trapped.

612
01:33:21,036 --> 01:33:23,287
To give light to them.

613
01:33:23,455 --> 01:33:25,456
Deliver us from evil.

614
01:33:25,624 --> 01:33:27,834
Not sit in darkness.

615
01:33:29,169 --> 01:33:32,130
Deal not with us after our sins.

616
01:33:34,300 --> 01:33:35,801
All thy people.

617
01:33:35,969 --> 01:33:40,222
I have become, as it were,
a monster unto many.

618
01:33:40,974 --> 01:33:43,100
Cast me not away.

619
01:33:46,730 --> 01:33:48,981
Make me a clean heart.

620
01:34:02,996 --> 01:34:04,997
[HOLLERING IN DISTANCE]

621
01:34:30,524 --> 01:34:31,858
ARGALL:
Tell him.

622
01:34:32,026 --> 01:34:33,902
The princess is up the river at Pastancy.

623
01:34:34,111 --> 01:34:35,987
They sent her
to her Uncle Patowomeck...

624
01:34:36,155 --> 01:34:38,239
...lord of the naked devils
of that region...

625
01:34:38,407 --> 01:34:40,408
...and, by the by,
an acquaintance of mine.

626
01:34:40,618 --> 01:34:43,536
So I get talking to his nibs,
and he proposes to sell her.

627
01:34:43,704 --> 01:34:46,873
He says with her at the fort,
the emperor will not dare attack us.

628
01:34:47,041 --> 01:34:49,709
- He dotes on her.
- You're certain she's the one you saw?

629
01:34:49,877 --> 01:34:52,879
With these eyes.
I spoke to the king directly.

630
01:34:53,047 --> 01:34:55,381
And what does this rogue
propose to sell her for?

631
01:34:55,549 --> 01:34:58,551
Well, I was getting to that.
His most favorite thing is combs.

632
01:34:58,719 --> 01:35:01,846
But in this case, he seems to have
his heart set on a kettle.

633
01:35:02,014 --> 01:35:05,183
You know, a copper kettle,
like my mother had for making stew.

634
01:35:05,351 --> 01:35:09,062
What use he means to make
of the instrument I cannot say.

635
01:35:12,066 --> 01:35:13,858
Well?

636
01:35:14,026 --> 01:35:15,902
We don't take hostages.

637
01:35:16,071 --> 01:35:17,571
King James would not approve.

638
01:35:17,739 --> 01:35:21,242
- You'd rather see us annihilated?
- She's done enough for us.

639
01:35:22,410 --> 01:35:25,204
She risked the beating in
of her own brains to save mine.

640
01:35:25,372 --> 01:35:26,831
Come, Argall, threaten me!

641
01:35:26,998 --> 01:35:29,500
Had she not fed us,
you would have starved.

642
01:35:29,668 --> 01:35:31,418
Then I'd know I was gonna live
for 1000 years.

643
01:35:31,586 --> 01:35:34,088
She's been the instrument
to preserve this colony from disaster.

644
01:35:34,256 --> 01:35:37,591
I'll not return her kindness
by making her a captive.

645
01:35:37,759 --> 01:35:41,804
She and her lot
are on the verge of killing us all.

646
01:35:43,765 --> 01:35:48,185
I expect there will be scarce a handful alive
when the boats return, if they ever do.

647
01:35:49,062 --> 01:35:52,606
You told us yourself that her father
regards her as no one else.

648
01:35:56,695 --> 01:36:00,489
Or do you have private reasons
for this attitude of yours?

649
01:36:03,952 --> 01:36:05,953
Return to your post.

650
01:36:10,293 --> 01:36:13,670
The penalty for disobeying
an order of the president is hanging.

651
01:36:13,838 --> 01:36:15,463
You're breaking the laws.

652
01:36:15,631 --> 01:36:17,632
This is mutiny.

653
01:36:18,009 --> 01:36:19,593
Me breaking the laws.

654
01:36:23,389 --> 01:36:26,349
I have information Smith here...

655
01:36:27,143 --> 01:36:31,730
...is planning to marry the wench
and make himself king of Virginia.

656
01:36:39,614 --> 01:36:41,615
[SHOUTING]

657
01:36:44,994 --> 01:36:47,579
You're no longer in command, Smitty.

658
01:36:47,747 --> 01:36:50,332
I shall wear the medal now.

659
01:36:50,499 --> 01:36:53,126
You've been derelict
in your duties to the king.

660
01:36:53,294 --> 01:36:55,670
You've betrayed
these citizens of Jamestown.

661
01:36:56,672 --> 01:36:59,258
I therefore pronounce you unwon'thy...

662
01:36:59,468 --> 01:37:01,177
...of being a member of this colony.

663
01:37:01,345 --> 01:37:02,845
You are no longer in command, Smitty!

664
01:37:03,013 --> 01:37:04,096
[WHIP CRACKING]

665
01:37:04,264 --> 01:37:08,768
Oh, oh, high and mighty, lord and ruler.

666
01:37:08,936 --> 01:37:10,686
No! No!

667
01:37:10,854 --> 01:37:12,939
We must have order, huh?

668
01:37:13,106 --> 01:37:14,982
We can't have everyone
running around...

669
01:37:15,150 --> 01:37:17,193
...giving themselves airs and graces...

670
01:37:17,361 --> 01:37:19,779
...because then...
Then we would have chaos, huh?

671
01:37:20,364 --> 01:37:22,782
- Scream.
POCAHONTAS: Come near.

672
01:37:23,033 --> 01:37:24,992
- Getting the strokes.
POCAHONTAS: Come near me.

673
01:37:25,202 --> 01:37:27,745
You say... You say,
"Friend, friend, dear friend...

674
01:37:27,913 --> 01:37:30,039
...I pray to the gods...
POCAHONTAS: You touch me now.

675
01:37:30,207 --> 01:37:33,334
...for your good health
for the rest of my life, I will."

676
01:37:34,920 --> 01:37:36,462
No man shows me disrespect.

677
01:37:36,630 --> 01:37:38,214
POCAHONTAS:
In all things...

678
01:37:39,299 --> 01:37:41,175
...may I stand by you.

679
01:37:41,343 --> 01:37:42,927
Put him to hard labor.

680
01:37:44,304 --> 01:37:49,058
Send him to the forest
to hew fresh timbers for the walls.

681
01:37:51,145 --> 01:37:53,480
Set him by the heels
each night when he's done...

682
01:37:53,648 --> 01:37:56,650
...that through the long watches
he might reflect on his transgressions.

683
01:38:05,034 --> 01:38:07,035
[MAN SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

684
01:38:27,265 --> 01:38:29,266
[ALL SHOUTING]

685
01:39:17,900 --> 01:39:19,650
MAN:
Put it down!

686
01:39:19,818 --> 01:39:21,819
Look behind you!

687
01:39:21,987 --> 01:39:23,988
[NATIVES HOLLERING]

688
01:39:27,159 --> 01:39:31,788
SELWAY: Move back.
Now you are the future, barking dog!

689
01:39:36,127 --> 01:39:37,961
POCAHONTAS:
Oh, Mother...

690
01:39:38,129 --> 01:39:41,173
...has he sent this ship for me?

691
01:39:49,015 --> 01:39:51,683
Conscience is nuisance.

692
01:39:52,852 --> 01:39:55,020
A fly.

693
01:39:55,438 --> 01:39:58,023
A barking dog.

694
01:39:59,275 --> 01:40:01,276
If you don't believe you have one...

695
01:40:01,444 --> 01:40:04,279
...what trouble can it be to you?

696
01:40:19,838 --> 01:40:21,797
POCAHONTAS:
Mother...

697
01:40:23,007 --> 01:40:26,136
...you are my strength...

698
01:40:27,680 --> 01:40:29,973
...or I have none.

699
01:40:50,744 --> 01:40:53,413
MAN:
Throw us your forward line!

700
01:40:59,086 --> 01:41:00,920
The president.

701
01:41:01,297 --> 01:41:03,923
Yes, I neglected to tell you.

702
01:41:04,758 --> 01:41:07,760
The captairs no longer
occupying that post.

703
01:41:08,095 --> 01:41:11,431
He will be able to explain the reasons
better than I.

704
01:41:51,473 --> 01:41:53,390
It's the princess.

705
01:42:03,026 --> 01:42:04,818
This will be your house, my lady.

706
01:42:04,986 --> 01:42:07,155
Reverend Whitaker,
the one what lived here...

707
01:42:07,323 --> 01:42:09,991
...well, he's...
He's dead and gone now, so...

708
01:42:34,892 --> 01:42:36,893
[BELL RINGING]

709
01:43:31,908 --> 01:43:32,950
[CANNONS BOOMING]

710
01:43:33,118 --> 01:43:36,162
SMITH:
The ships returned, firing their cannons...

711
01:43:36,663 --> 01:43:39,749
...causing the naturals to sue for peace.

712
01:43:47,132 --> 01:43:49,134
[MEN CHEERING]

713
01:45:01,166 --> 01:45:03,668
They said they were going to fetch you.

714
01:45:04,169 --> 01:45:06,129
I was against it.

715
01:45:26,483 --> 01:45:28,651
I didn't wanna harm you.

716
01:45:30,320 --> 01:45:34,324
There's disaster all around. We should
have stopped before it was too late.

717
01:46:05,982 --> 01:46:08,233
POCAHONTAS:
What is right?

718
01:46:08,401 --> 01:46:10,402
Give.

719
01:46:10,570 --> 01:46:13,739
Wrong? Who is this man?

720
01:46:16,784 --> 01:46:18,494
Now...

721
01:46:20,455 --> 01:46:22,331
...all is perfect.

722
01:46:22,499 --> 01:46:24,209
Let me be lost.

723
01:46:24,376 --> 01:46:26,252
True.

724
01:46:26,420 --> 01:46:29,130
You flow through me...

725
01:46:31,342 --> 01:46:33,676
...like a river.

726
01:46:37,181 --> 01:46:38,973
Come.

727
01:46:40,768 --> 01:46:41,976
Follow me.

728
01:46:42,186 --> 01:46:44,187
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

729
01:46:50,903 --> 01:46:53,821
MAN:
Oh, Lord, thank you.

730
01:46:55,115 --> 01:46:57,033
Captain.

731
01:47:17,514 --> 01:47:19,431
Very well.

732
01:47:20,642 --> 01:47:22,518
Leave us alone.

733
01:47:25,730 --> 01:47:28,357
You wish to bring charges
against this man?

734
01:47:28,525 --> 01:47:30,568
Are you sure?

735
01:47:30,735 --> 01:47:34,446
Well, fine then, Argall,
enough of your quarrels. Be off.

736
01:47:42,831 --> 01:47:45,249
I have news for you.

737
01:47:46,334 --> 01:47:49,587
The king wants you
to return to England...

738
01:47:49,963 --> 01:47:52,673
...to prepare an expedition
of your own.

739
01:47:52,841 --> 01:47:55,259
To chart the northern coasts...

740
01:47:55,427 --> 01:47:59,305
...to see if you might find
a passage to the Indies.

741
01:48:00,348 --> 01:48:03,309
I remember when you had
sight and ambition.

742
01:48:03,476 --> 01:48:06,062
Shall you not press on?

743
01:48:06,814 --> 01:48:11,860
Shall you be a discoverer of passages
which you yourself refuse to explore...

744
01:48:12,028 --> 01:48:15,530
...beyond the threshold, that is?

745
01:48:17,199 --> 01:48:20,952
King has great hopes for you.
Plans.

746
01:48:26,167 --> 01:48:29,377
Um, she's to take care of you now.

747
01:48:29,545 --> 01:48:31,630
My name's Mary.

748
01:48:31,797 --> 01:48:33,506
- And yours, I believe is...
- Oh, no...

749
01:48:33,674 --> 01:48:36,051
...she says that's not
her name anymore.

750
01:48:36,218 --> 01:48:38,053
She hasn't got a name.

751
01:48:38,262 --> 01:48:40,013
How unfortunate.

752
01:48:40,181 --> 01:48:42,807
Well, we shall have to give you one.

753
01:48:54,487 --> 01:48:56,196
Here.

754
01:48:59,910 --> 01:49:01,994
Rub with the towel.

755
01:49:02,329 --> 01:49:06,582
POCAHONTAS:
I will find joy in all I see.

756
01:49:06,750 --> 01:49:09,251
Where am I going? Mother.

757
01:49:10,587 --> 01:49:12,922
- Fast.
MARY: Just little steps.

758
01:49:14,257 --> 01:49:16,008
POCAHONTAS:
So fast. I want my love.

759
01:49:16,176 --> 01:49:17,593
MARY:
Oh.

760
01:49:19,262 --> 01:49:21,138
POCAHONTAS:
To go to him.

761
01:49:21,306 --> 01:49:23,641
The river. Living water.

762
01:49:23,809 --> 01:49:25,518
To meet him.

763
01:49:26,436 --> 01:49:28,396
Where does it come from?

764
01:49:30,941 --> 01:49:32,400
Where is it going?

765
01:49:32,567 --> 01:49:35,027
Why do they want gold?

766
01:49:37,155 --> 01:49:39,407
Can't they make it?

767
01:49:43,286 --> 01:49:45,579
NEWPORT: We shall lose not only our lives...
- Do they eat it?

768
01:49:45,747 --> 01:49:47,123
NEWPORT:
...and our land...

769
01:49:47,290 --> 01:49:48,917
...but our eternal birthright.

770
01:49:49,085 --> 01:49:51,294
Look beyond these gates.

771
01:49:51,462 --> 01:49:53,255
Eden lies about us still.

772
01:49:54,173 --> 01:49:57,926
We have escaped the Old World
and its bondage.

773
01:49:58,094 --> 01:50:00,011
Let us make a new beginning...

774
01:50:00,179 --> 01:50:03,515
...and create a fresh example
for humanity.

775
01:50:03,683 --> 01:50:06,560
We are the pioneers of the world.

776
01:50:06,728 --> 01:50:09,312
The advance guard sent on
through the wilderness...

777
01:50:09,480 --> 01:50:12,065
...to break a new path.

778
01:50:13,943 --> 01:50:18,155
And our youth is our strength,
and our inexperience our wisdom.

779
01:50:19,115 --> 01:50:20,490
God has given us...

780
01:50:20,658 --> 01:50:24,286
...a promised land, a great ineritance.

781
01:50:24,454 --> 01:50:28,915
Woe betide if ever
we turn our back on him.

782
01:50:29,709 --> 01:50:34,129
Let us prepare a land
where a man may rise...

783
01:50:34,338 --> 01:50:35,630
...to his true stature.

784
01:50:35,840 --> 01:50:41,554
A land of the future,
a new kingdom of the spirit.

785
01:50:41,722 --> 01:50:44,557
Remember what this country was...

786
01:51:27,309 --> 01:51:29,560
POCAHONTAS:
Am I as you like?

787
01:51:33,817 --> 01:51:35,692
His eyes.

788
01:51:41,866 --> 01:51:45,536
You knew me as I was...

789
01:51:45,745 --> 01:51:47,663
...long ago.

790
01:51:49,874 --> 01:51:53,085
I have never truly been the man
I seem to you to be.

791
01:51:53,670 --> 01:51:55,921
POCAHONTAS:
What does he say?

792
01:51:56,089 --> 01:51:59,424
Come, let's sit by the river.

793
01:52:00,760 --> 01:52:02,678
Mean?

794
01:52:07,016 --> 01:52:10,269
I can't sleep till I see you again.

795
01:52:10,854 --> 01:52:11,895
Look up.

796
01:52:14,774 --> 01:52:16,900
You have no evil.

797
01:52:19,237 --> 01:52:21,738
I belong to you.

798
01:52:31,625 --> 01:52:33,793
He knows.

799
01:52:41,886 --> 01:52:43,803
Where am I?

800
01:53:00,905 --> 01:53:02,947
Wait two months...

801
01:53:03,824 --> 01:53:06,034
...then tell her I am dead.

802
01:53:06,577 --> 01:53:08,578
Drowned.

803
01:54:07,139 --> 01:54:08,473
[SOBBING]

804
01:54:48,806 --> 01:54:50,807
MARY:
Like that.

805
01:55:00,402 --> 01:55:03,446
He's left you, princess.

806
01:55:03,989 --> 01:55:06,198
He told you a pack of lies.

807
01:55:06,408 --> 01:55:08,451
Forget about him.

808
01:55:27,596 --> 01:55:30,890
SELWAY:
I, uh, have some terrible news.

809
01:55:33,143 --> 01:55:36,979
Captain Smith is dead.
He drowned in the crossing.

810
01:55:40,358 --> 01:55:42,693
He loved you very much.

811
01:56:28,533 --> 01:56:29,991
POCAHONTAS:
Unwed.

812
01:56:33,204 --> 01:56:35,622
Where is your love now?

813
01:56:42,673 --> 01:56:44,382
Where is our child?

814
01:56:52,224 --> 01:56:56,519
You have gone away with my life.

815
01:57:01,650 --> 01:57:04,360
Killed the god in me.

816
01:57:15,581 --> 01:57:17,790
[SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

817
01:58:09,302 --> 01:58:11,845
POCAHONTAS:
Does the sun see this?

818
01:58:34,119 --> 01:58:37,664
On the bed of fate, we lie.

819
01:58:43,837 --> 01:58:45,838
[SPEAKING IN ALGONQUIN]

820
01:58:54,181 --> 01:58:56,349
We can enter you.

821
01:58:59,770 --> 01:59:01,771
Question you.

822
01:59:10,197 --> 01:59:12,031
I mourn.

823
01:59:14,244 --> 01:59:16,036
I grieve.

824
01:59:20,000 --> 01:59:22,543
Take my hand, Father.

825
02:00:29,487 --> 02:00:31,279
Scorned.

826
02:00:32,573 --> 02:00:35,033
Cast out, cut off.

827
02:00:36,285 --> 02:00:38,119
A dog.

828
02:00:43,417 --> 02:00:46,419
Come, death.

829
02:00:47,004 --> 02:00:48,838
Take me.

830
02:00:51,425 --> 02:00:53,426
Set me free.

831
02:00:58,517 --> 02:01:01,185
Let me be what I was.

832
02:01:16,410 --> 02:01:17,827
[BIRD CHIRPING]

833
02:04:17,677 --> 02:04:19,678
[CROWD CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

834
02:04:48,375 --> 02:04:53,463
ROLFE: When first I saw her,
she was regarded as someone finished.

835
02:04:53,964 --> 02:04:56,758
Broken, lost.

836
02:05:06,143 --> 02:05:09,395
She seemed barely to notice
the others about her.

837
02:05:34,255 --> 02:05:37,966
Um, I would like to spend
the afternoon with you.

838
02:05:42,097 --> 02:05:44,056
How do I ask?

839
02:05:49,604 --> 02:05:54,191
MARY: A nature like yours
can turn trouble into good.

840
02:05:55,944 --> 02:05:58,987
All this sorrow will give you strength...

841
02:05:59,197 --> 02:06:02,032
...and point you on a higher way.

842
02:06:03,244 --> 02:06:08,164
Think of a tree,
how it grows around its wounds.

843
02:06:08,332 --> 02:06:11,835
If a branch breaks off, it don't stop...

844
02:06:12,002 --> 02:06:16,256
...but keeps reaching towards the light.

845
02:06:17,466 --> 02:06:22,971
We must meet misfortune boldly,
and not suffer it to frighten us.

846
02:06:23,889 --> 02:06:26,558
We must act the play out...

847
02:06:26,726 --> 02:06:30,562
...then live our troubles down, my lady.

848
02:06:43,242 --> 02:06:45,285
April, May...

849
02:06:45,453 --> 02:06:48,997
...and June, July, August.

850
02:06:49,165 --> 02:06:52,250
- What is a day?
- A day?

851
02:06:52,418 --> 02:06:54,503
An hour?

852
02:06:54,755 --> 02:06:57,381
An hour is 60 minutes.

853
02:06:59,217 --> 02:07:01,969
Why does the earth have colors?

854
02:07:28,038 --> 02:07:30,706
ROLFE:
Many passions have I endured.

855
02:07:31,833 --> 02:07:34,877
Daily, hourly.

856
02:07:36,379 --> 02:07:38,464
Even in my sleep.

857
02:07:40,550 --> 02:07:43,219
Awaking me to astonishment.

858
02:07:44,054 --> 02:07:46,556
This love has become...

859
02:07:47,225 --> 02:07:49,476
...such a labyrinth...

860
02:07:49,769 --> 02:07:52,395
...that I no longer know...
POCAHONTAS: Were you sad...

861
02:07:52,563 --> 02:07:54,564
ROLFE:
...how to wind myself out from it.

862
02:07:54,732 --> 02:07:57,359
POCAHONTAS:
...to lose your wife and daughter?

863
02:08:04,742 --> 02:08:06,243
NEWPORT:
Name this person.

864
02:08:06,744 --> 02:08:08,245
Rebecca.

865
02:08:08,412 --> 02:08:10,413
NEWPORT [WHISPERING]:
Rebecca, I baptize thee...

866
02:08:10,581 --> 02:08:13,041
...in the name
of the Father and the Son...

867
02:08:13,209 --> 02:08:16,628
...and the Holy Ghost. Amen.

868
02:08:21,759 --> 02:08:24,261
ROLFE: She has accepted my invitation
to work in the fields.

869
02:08:24,428 --> 02:08:25,929
WOMAN 1:
For Rebecca.

870
02:08:26,097 --> 02:08:27,931
WOMAN 2:
She'll be missed.

871
02:08:28,099 --> 02:08:30,767
ROLFE: She understands
the culture of tobacco.

872
02:08:30,935 --> 02:08:32,936
WOMAN 3:
She's a good lass.

873
02:08:36,440 --> 02:08:39,443
ROLFE:
The people were sorry at her going.

874
02:08:50,372 --> 02:08:52,373
[CHICKENS CLUCKING]

875
02:09:55,688 --> 02:09:58,023
Hours pass.

876
02:09:58,691 --> 02:10:01,485
She speaks not a word.

877
02:10:49,410 --> 02:10:51,244
Who are you?

878
02:10:54,790 --> 02:10:56,791
What do you dream of?

879
02:10:59,420 --> 02:11:01,421
We're like grass.

880
02:11:19,691 --> 02:11:21,608
Are you kind?

881
02:12:14,330 --> 02:12:17,332
She weaves all things together.

882
02:12:23,798 --> 02:12:26,341
I touched her long ago...

883
02:12:26,842 --> 02:12:29,385
...without knowing her name.

884
02:12:50,032 --> 02:12:52,242
All sings to her.

885
02:12:54,079 --> 02:12:56,080
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

886
02:13:10,595 --> 02:13:13,389
Suppose I asked you to marry me.
What would you say?

887
02:13:19,020 --> 02:13:21,021
Are you asking me?

888
02:13:24,359 --> 02:13:26,485
Where would we live?

889
02:13:26,653 --> 02:13:28,320
Here.

890
02:13:29,573 --> 02:13:34,285
England, if you wish.
Perhaps that would be best. We could...

891
02:13:34,536 --> 02:13:37,705
Well, you could forget your life
in this place.

892
02:13:53,097 --> 02:13:55,348
Why do you shrink from me?

893
02:14:00,271 --> 02:14:02,772
Wort you say yes?

894
02:14:09,071 --> 02:14:11,072
If you like.

895
02:14:14,368 --> 02:14:16,828
This isn't what I expected.

896
02:14:16,996 --> 02:14:18,455
Rebecca.

897
02:14:20,249 --> 02:14:22,042
I'm sorry.

898
02:14:24,253 --> 02:14:27,130
Why are you crying?

899
02:14:31,219 --> 02:14:33,386
I suppose...

900
02:14:34,555 --> 02:14:36,766
...I must be happy.

901
02:14:39,478 --> 02:14:41,938
You do not love me now.

902
02:14:42,689 --> 02:14:44,815
Someday you will.

903
02:14:58,747 --> 02:15:01,582
MAN: You're not ignorant to the displeasure
which God conceived...

904
02:15:01,750 --> 02:15:06,712
...against the sons of Levi and Israel
for marrying strange wives.

905
02:15:07,506 --> 02:15:09,006
No.

906
02:15:09,716 --> 02:15:12,843
GOVERNOR: Would you do anything
necessary to bring this about?

907
02:15:13,345 --> 02:15:14,679
Yes.

908
02:15:18,934 --> 02:15:20,810
GOVERNOR:
Would you write a petition...

909
02:15:20,978 --> 02:15:23,104
...explaining as the wealthiest
planter in Virginia...

910
02:15:23,272 --> 02:15:26,148
ROLFE: The governor requires a letter...
GOVERNOR: The benefit?

911
02:15:26,316 --> 02:15:29,528
ROLFE:
...stating acceptable reasons for our union.

912
02:15:29,696 --> 02:15:33,699
Could you state your hope that this might
begin the work of converting the naturals?

913
02:15:33,866 --> 02:15:37,703
That this idea came to you in no way
through any carnal affection...

914
02:15:38,913 --> 02:15:43,375
...but for the good of the plantation.
For the honor of your country.

915
02:15:43,543 --> 02:15:46,295
And your own soul.

916
02:15:47,130 --> 02:15:50,465
ROLFE: Humiliated.
- To save an unbelieving creature...

917
02:15:50,633 --> 02:15:53,218
ROLFE:
And yet he does not touch me.

918
02:15:54,554 --> 02:15:56,972
GOVERNOR:
If this be not your true intent...

919
02:15:57,140 --> 02:15:59,099
...would you do that?

920
02:16:00,476 --> 02:16:01,977
Yes.

921
02:16:03,354 --> 02:16:07,149
NEWPORT:
Then surely you do love her, Mr. Rolfe.

922
02:16:12,780 --> 02:16:14,364
Write.

923
02:16:28,922 --> 02:16:30,715
NEWPORT:
I require and charge you...

924
02:16:30,883 --> 02:16:34,427
...as you will answer
on the dreadful Day of Judgment...

925
02:16:34,636 --> 02:16:38,931
...when the secrets
of all hearts are disclosed...

926
02:16:39,975 --> 02:16:42,685
...that if you know any impediment...

927
02:16:42,853 --> 02:16:47,231
...why you should not be
lawfully joined together in matrimony...

928
02:16:47,399 --> 02:16:49,108
...you will confess it.

929
02:16:49,276 --> 02:16:51,611
[BELL RINGING]

930
02:18:03,978 --> 02:18:05,812
POCAHONTAS:
Mother...

931
02:18:06,939 --> 02:18:09,357
...why can I not feel as I should?

932
02:18:13,821 --> 02:18:15,530
Must?

933
02:18:22,121 --> 02:18:24,164
Once false...

934
02:18:24,331 --> 02:18:27,125
...I must not be again.

935
02:18:32,047 --> 02:18:34,674
Take out the thorn.

936
02:18:45,478 --> 02:18:47,479
[ROLFE LAUGHING]

937
02:18:48,856 --> 02:18:51,274
He is like a tree.

938
02:18:53,778 --> 02:18:56,155
He shelters me.

939
02:18:59,075 --> 02:19:01,660
I lie in his shade.

940
02:19:20,305 --> 02:19:23,057
Can I ignore my heart?

941
02:19:32,400 --> 02:19:34,818
What is from you...

942
02:19:35,195 --> 02:19:37,530
...and what is not?

943
02:20:05,309 --> 02:20:08,979
Great Sun, I offer you thanks.

944
02:20:10,022 --> 02:20:11,815
You give life to the trees...

945
02:20:12,525 --> 02:20:14,401
...and hills.

946
02:20:16,654 --> 02:20:19,114
To the streams of water.

947
02:20:22,410 --> 02:20:24,160
To all.

948
02:20:25,830 --> 02:20:27,831
[SINGING INDISTINCTLY]

949
02:20:34,881 --> 02:20:36,591
[CRYING]

950
02:20:50,022 --> 02:20:51,772
Mother...

951
02:20:53,025 --> 02:20:54,442
...your love...

952
02:20:54,610 --> 02:20:57,153
...is before my eyes.

953
02:21:00,991 --> 02:21:03,284
Show me your way.

954
02:21:06,496 --> 02:21:08,956
Teach me your path.

955
02:21:14,212 --> 02:21:18,007
Give me a humble heart.

956
02:21:18,175 --> 02:21:20,843
ROLFE:
We've had some surprising news.

957
02:21:21,970 --> 02:21:23,512
We've been invited to England...

958
02:21:23,680 --> 02:21:24,722
[CHILD LAUGHS]

959
02:21:24,890 --> 02:21:26,642
...by the king and queen.

960
02:21:29,562 --> 02:21:31,396
There will be...

961
02:21:31,564 --> 02:21:34,191
...a royal audience in your honor.

962
02:21:36,235 --> 02:21:37,819
You're known to them all.

963
02:22:39,466 --> 02:22:41,467
[WOMAN SPEAKING IN INUIT]

964
02:23:03,449 --> 02:23:06,701
WOMAN: Gave him up to pirates
when his ship was stopped.

965
02:23:06,869 --> 02:23:08,996
Five years before he could
get a commission.

966
02:23:09,164 --> 02:23:11,498
Five years.

967
02:23:14,669 --> 02:23:16,670
All them ships
went off to Newfoundland.

968
02:23:16,838 --> 02:23:18,505
MAN: Yes.
WOMAN: Who would have guessed?

969
02:23:18,673 --> 02:23:21,508
He poked around the north,
then he went home.

970
02:23:21,676 --> 02:23:23,469
Captain Smith.

971
02:23:24,387 --> 02:23:26,180
Yeah, he could make you laugh.

972
02:23:27,056 --> 02:23:29,057
MAN:
Things are different now.

973
02:23:29,851 --> 02:23:31,518
WOMAN:
They've sent him back to London.

974
02:23:31,686 --> 02:23:35,522
What a shame. They say
he's done much for this place.

975
02:23:39,527 --> 02:23:42,362
POCAHONTAS:
Captain Smith is alive?

976
02:23:45,533 --> 02:23:47,576
You saw him?

977
02:24:49,431 --> 02:24:51,433
I cannot do that.

978
02:24:52,435 --> 02:24:53,936
Why not?

979
02:24:55,438 --> 02:24:59,859
It would mean something I do not feel.

980
02:25:00,777 --> 02:25:02,570
What's come over you?

981
02:25:05,824 --> 02:25:07,700
I'm married...

982
02:25:08,285 --> 02:25:10,077
...to him.

983
02:25:10,954 --> 02:25:12,621
He lives.

984
02:25:13,498 --> 02:25:15,708
I heard it by the fort.

985
02:25:16,793 --> 02:25:18,794
He's still alive.

986
02:25:23,466 --> 02:25:25,134
Married?

987
02:25:25,594 --> 02:25:29,346
You don't know the meaning
of the word exactly.

988
02:25:31,141 --> 02:25:32,808
But I am.

989
02:25:51,913 --> 02:25:53,872
ROLFE:
Sweet wife...

990
02:25:59,253 --> 02:26:01,922
...love made the bond.

991
02:26:02,798 --> 02:26:05,675
Love can break it too.

992
02:26:28,866 --> 02:26:31,076
There is that in her...

993
02:26:31,243 --> 02:26:33,578
...I shall not know.

994
02:26:39,044 --> 02:26:41,045
[CREW CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

995
02:26:54,267 --> 02:26:55,893
[IN ALGONQUIN]

996
02:27:28,886 --> 02:27:30,887
[CROWD CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

997
02:28:14,640 --> 02:28:16,642
[MEN CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

998
02:28:20,314 --> 02:28:22,315
[HORSES WHINNYING]

999
02:28:53,680 --> 02:28:55,223
[HORSE GRUNTING]

1000
02:29:11,074 --> 02:29:13,367
MAN:
Stand aside, I say!

1001
02:29:16,371 --> 02:29:18,372
[BELL RINGING]

1002
02:30:27,359 --> 02:30:28,860
POET:
- Homage sweetly pay

1003
02:30:29,028 --> 02:30:31,446
Whilst towering in the azure sky

1004
02:30:31,614 --> 02:30:34,115
They celebrate this happy day.

1005
02:30:34,283 --> 02:30:37,035
Let rolling streams their gladness show

1006
02:30:37,203 --> 02:30:39,871
With gentle murmurs whilst they play

1007
02:30:40,039 --> 02:30:42,415
And in their wild meanders flow

1008
02:30:42,583 --> 02:30:45,752
Rejoicing in this blessed day.

1009
02:30:45,920 --> 02:30:48,922
Kind health descends on downy wings

1010
02:30:49,089 --> 02:30:51,383
Angels conduct her on the way

1011
02:30:51,551 --> 02:30:54,220
The New World's Princess
New life brings

1012
02:30:54,387 --> 02:30:56,972
And swells our joys upon this day.

1013
02:31:29,464 --> 02:31:31,465
[SQUAWKING]

1014
02:33:18,909 --> 02:33:20,618
POCAHONTAS:
Mother...

1015
02:33:21,411 --> 02:33:23,496
...stay near me.

1016
02:33:30,797 --> 02:33:33,465
[IN ALGONQUIN]

1017
02:35:09,522 --> 02:35:11,398
ROLFE:
Sweet wife...

1018
02:35:12,734 --> 02:35:15,277
...do you care for me still?

1019
02:35:23,745 --> 02:35:27,539
I cannot be to you what I am not.

1020
02:35:31,419 --> 02:35:35,589
She would never have married me
had she known that he were alive.

1021
02:35:40,053 --> 02:35:44,348
She bound herself to me in ignorance,
and I will not...

1022
02:35:45,141 --> 02:35:49,436
I will not let her be encumbered
by a tie which she despises...

1023
02:35:49,604 --> 02:35:51,605
...and enter to her mischief.

1024
02:35:54,442 --> 02:35:56,443
I will do nothing against her will.

1025
02:36:34,567 --> 02:36:36,985
ROLFE:
I think you still love the man...

1026
02:36:37,444 --> 02:36:41,447
...and that you will not be at peace
until you see him.

1027
02:36:43,158 --> 02:36:46,744
In my vanity, I thought...

1028
02:36:47,788 --> 02:36:49,247
...I could make you love me...

1029
02:36:49,416 --> 02:36:53,919
...and one cannot do that, or should not.

1030
02:36:59,467 --> 02:37:01,760
You have walked...

1031
02:37:02,470 --> 02:37:04,138
...blindly...

1032
02:37:04,306 --> 02:37:06,724
...into a situation
that you did not anticipate.

1033
02:37:06,891 --> 02:37:11,186
I will not rob you of your self-respect.

1034
02:37:22,240 --> 02:37:25,117
You are the man I thought you were.

1035
02:37:27,078 --> 02:37:28,871
And more.

1036
02:38:34,606 --> 02:38:37,108
SMITH:
Did I make a mistake in coming here?

1037
02:38:39,444 --> 02:38:41,445
I would have come before...

1038
02:38:41,613 --> 02:38:43,906
...except I've been
away from the capital.

1039
02:38:48,078 --> 02:38:52,039
Perhaps I'm out of order
speaking with you this way...

1040
02:38:54,000 --> 02:38:56,460
...but I've thought of you often.

1041
02:39:01,299 --> 02:39:04,635
So after I left, it went well for you.

1042
02:39:06,138 --> 02:39:08,055
I heard the king and queen received you.

1043
02:39:08,223 --> 02:39:10,266
Everybody says you were
a great favorite.

1044
02:39:10,434 --> 02:39:12,852
They all speak of you.
One hears them in the streets.

1045
02:39:13,019 --> 02:39:16,564
"Her Ladyship."
Who would have guessed it?

1046
02:39:59,609 --> 02:40:01,193
You knew...

1047
02:40:01,360 --> 02:40:03,445
...I had promise.

1048
02:40:03,821 --> 02:40:06,865
- Didrt you?
- Yes.

1049
02:40:17,127 --> 02:40:19,378
Did you find your Indies, John?

1050
02:40:26,512 --> 02:40:28,471
You shall.

1051
02:40:40,234 --> 02:40:42,652
I may have sailed past them.

1052
02:41:02,714 --> 02:41:05,258
I thought it was a dream...

1053
02:41:06,261 --> 02:41:08,679
...what we knew in the forest.

1054
02:41:11,266 --> 02:41:13,600
It's the only truth.

1055
02:41:20,900 --> 02:41:24,236
It seems as if I were
speaking to you for the first time.

1056
02:43:06,132 --> 02:43:08,384
Could we not go home?

1057
02:43:10,887 --> 02:43:13,222
As soon as possible.

1058
02:43:30,115 --> 02:43:32,408
[WHISPERING]
My husband.

1059
02:44:31,720 --> 02:44:33,596
THOMAS [WHISPERING]:
Listen.

1060
02:44:35,557 --> 02:44:37,391
[WHISPERING INAUDIBLY]

1061
02:44:46,526 --> 02:44:48,069
[LAUGHS]

1062
02:44:59,498 --> 02:45:01,123
Thomas.

1063
02:45:01,666 --> 02:45:02,666
Where?

1064
02:45:20,685 --> 02:45:22,521
Mother...

1065
02:45:22,814 --> 02:45:25,107
...now I know where you live.

1066
02:45:25,566 --> 02:45:27,567
[LAUGHING]

1067
02:45:32,824 --> 02:45:35,826
ROLFE:
Thirteenth of April, 1616.

1068
02:45:36,035 --> 02:45:38,078
THOMAS: Mother. Mother.
ROLFE: Dear son:

1069
02:45:38,246 --> 02:45:40,372
I write this so that someday
in the future...

1070
02:45:40,540 --> 02:45:42,457
...you might understand
a circumstance...

1071
02:45:42,625 --> 02:45:46,086
...which shall be
but a far memory to you.

1072
02:45:49,215 --> 02:45:51,091
Your dear mother, Rebecca...

1073
02:45:51,259 --> 02:45:53,844
...fell ill in our outward passage...

1074
02:45:54,011 --> 02:45:55,554
...at Gravesend.

1075
02:45:59,976 --> 02:46:02,853
She gently reminded me that all must die.

1076
02:46:03,020 --> 02:46:07,440
"'Tis enough," she said, "that you,
our child, should live."

1077
02:51:46,996 --> 02:51:48,997
[ENGLISH SDH]

